The paper discusses the impact of boundary effects on the connectivity of wireless networks, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also presents an analytical framework for analyzing the connectivity of the network, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential of the proposed approach for more general non-convex geometries, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM).
